Name: Baroque Churches of the Philippines
Description: Baroque Churches of the Philippines - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Four Spanish colonial churches showcasing Philippine Baroque architecture.

Name: Tubbataha Reefs Natural Park
Description: Tubbataha Reefs Natural Park - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Marine sanctuary with pristine coral reefs and diverse marine life.

Name: Rice Terraces of the Philippine Cordilleras
Description: Rice Terraces of the Philippine Cordilleras - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient terraced rice fields carved into mountains by Ifugao people.

Name: Historic City of Vigan
Description: Historic City of Vigan - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Best-preserved example of a planned Spanish colonial town in Asia.

Name: Puerto-Princesa Subterranean River National Park
Description: Puerto-Princesa Subterranean River National Park - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Underground river flowing through limestone karst landscape.

Name: Mount Hamiguitan Range Wildlife Sanctuary
Description: Mount Hamiguitan Range Wildlife Sanctuary - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Mountain range with unique pygmy forest ecosystem.
